The paper deals with query answering on graph databases, which is a topic closely related to database management systems (cs.DB). The use of Regular Path Queries (RPQ) and the mention of Datalog suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the rewriting query, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of computational complexity (cs.CR). Finally, the use of graph databases and regular languages may also make the paper relevant to researchers in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
